<item>
            <title>[OAK-1927] TarMK compaction delays journal updates</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1927</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The compaction operation gets currently invoked from the TarMK flush thread, which is a bit troublesome as the operation can take some while during which the flush thread won&apos;t be able to persist the latest updates to the journal file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To avoid this problem, the compaction operation should be performed in a separate background thread.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
